article_title: Dunkin’ Can’t Glaze Over Competition -- Ahead of the Tape
article_text:
Last weekend’s Super Bowl outcome was sweet revenge for Dunkin’ Brands Group Inc.

Not only is the chain a sponsor of the victorious New England Patriots, but the contest was seized upon by two Dunkin’ rivals: Southeast-based Krispy Kreme Doughnuts Inc. had poked fun at the “deflategate” controversy dogging the Pats before the game with a football-themed campaign insisting their doughnuts “are fully filled.” Meanwhile, Seattle-based...
